TITLE: OASIS: Orchestration of Adaptive SFC with Intelligent Sensing for Environment-Aware Multi-RAT Networks

DOMAIN: 5G/6G Networks, Network Function Virtualization (NFV), Service Function Chaining (SFC), Multi-Radio Access Technology (Multi-RAT)

CORE PROBLEM:
Traditional cloud orchestration frameworks are static and focus only on resource availability. They fail to consider dynamic QoS requirements for different service flows, deployment constraints, and operator policies in heterogeneous Multi-RAT environments (4G, 5G, Wi-Fi coexistence).

PROPOSED SOLUTION - OASIS FRAMEWORK:
A plugin-based, extensible orchestration framework that uses:
1. Graph Attention Network (GAT) for topology-aware node embeddings
2. Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) with PPO for optimal CNF placement
3. LSTM-based time-series forecasting for predictive vertical scaling
4. Segment Routing (SRv6/SR-MPLS) for inter-NF transport

KEY TECHNICAL CONTRIBUTIONS:
- Three-dimensional orchestration model: (1) Multi-RAT SFC flows, (2) QoS/deployment constraints, (3) Operator policies
- GAT-based infrastructure modeling with custom distance metrics for node compatibility
- DRL agent with continuous action space for microservice placement
- Delayed reward function incorporating QoS (PDB, PER), resource (CPU, memory), and energy constraints
- QoS-aware traffic steering using Cloud-Native Load Balancer (CNLB)
- LSTM-based traffic forecasting for adaptive vertical scaling

KEY RESULTS:
- 19.4% reduction in CPU usage
- 35.25% reduction in memory usage
- SLA compliance for QFI flows 2 (URLLC) and 79 (eMBB)
- Reduced cluster peak utilization and energy consumption

